HEADWORD: Tiling
<hw>Til"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A surface
covered with tiles, or composed of tiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They . . . let him down through the <qex>tiling</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke v. 19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tiles, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Till</ent>⟦br⟧
